
prototype
......
used to create new objects by cloning an existing object instead of creating them from scratch.


Why Prototype Pattern?
..................................................
Suppose creating an object is expensive:

Employee emp = new Employee();
emp.loadDataFromDatabase(); // Expensive operation

Instead of loading data again:

Employee emp2 = emp.clone();

We create a copy of the existing object.
..................................................

implement cloanable interface
 and override clone method to create a copy of the object.
 return super.clone() to create a shallow copy of the object.
 override toString method for easy display of object information.
............................................................
class Employee implements Cloneable {

    private int id;
    private String name;

    public Employee(int id, String name) {
        this.id = id;
        this.name = name;
    }

    @Override
    protected Object clone() throws CloneNotSupportedException {

        return super.clone();
    }

    @Override
    public String toString() {
        return id + " " + name;
    }
}



Feature           	Shallow Copy	                                       Deep Copy
Object Copied	   Main object only	                                       Main + nested objects
Memory Usage	     Less memory	                                       More memory
Performance	         Faster	                                               Slower
                    changes will effect the original object	               changes not affect the original object


